## Available Wrappers Quick Reference

| Wrapper | Use case | Vault needed |
|---|---|---|
| `stripe_wrapper` | Stripe customers, subscriptions, invoices | Stripe secret key |
| `firebase_wrapper` | Firestore documents, Firebase Auth users | Service account JSON |
| `s3_wrapper` | CSV/Parquet files in AWS S3 or R2 | AWS credentials |
| `bigquery_wrapper` | BigQuery tables and views | GCP service account |
| `clickhouse_wrapper` | ClickHouse analytics tables | CH credentials |
| `airtable_wrapper` | Airtable base tables | Airtable API key |
| `redis_wrapper` | Redis key-value, sorted sets | Redis URL |
| `notion_wrapper` | Notion databases | Notion API key |
| `cognito_wrapper` | AWS Cognito user pools | AWS credentials |

All wrappers: always use Vault for credentials, always use private schema for tables.

